1
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,799
While we're at school,
we should keep our distance.

2
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,279
Sometimes we must push through
and do things we don't enjoy.

3
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:38,719
If we see the benefit in it,

4
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:41,200
we just carry on
and do what we must.

5
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:44,280
"Saeng Karun Foundation."

6
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:56,480
I wanted to apologize for...

7
00:00:56,500 --> 00:01:00,270
not being able to take care
of Saeng Karun well enough.

8
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:02,130
Don't blame yourself.

9
00:01:02,690 --> 00:01:04,760
Everything has its causes.

10
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,200
Dad.

11
00:01:36,070 --> 00:01:38,920
When you're done,
put it away in the cabinet.

12
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,920
I hooked up a buzzer for you.

13
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,120
No need to blow your lungs out.

14
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,120
I am used to it.

15
00:01:48,530 --> 00:01:53,500
Fine. But if you keel over,
don't complain to me.

16
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:56,880
Gotta work.

17
00:02:08,390 --> 00:02:09,390
Hey.

18
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:27,280
Hello, yes. This is Somsak.

19
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:30,080
I'd like to ask about my loan.

20
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,560
Of course, sir.

21
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,640
I was actually just
about to call you.

22
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:38,800
If I can't make a payment,
what can the bank do for me?

23
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:41,720
We're happy to
discuss your options, sir.

24
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,160
But may I ask you something first?

25
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:47,230
You mentioned before that
a sum of money was coming in.

26
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:48,840
Has something come up?

27
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,720
Just tell me straight.
What do I need to do?

28
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:54,900
Right now, I have no money.

29
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:11,640
Grandpa, I've got
some juicy gossip for you.

30
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:13,620
Hmm?

31
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:17,590
Guy said he'd keep trying to
win me over, right?

32
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:19,800
Mm-hmm.

33
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:21,360
He does flirt with me every day.

34
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:25,220
He's like...
pulls something new every day.

35
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,560
Never the same move twice.

36
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:29,390
Grandpa.

37
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,760
Not taking notes?

38
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,920
I'm done writing BL novels.

39
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,680
What do you mean?

40
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:44,320
Are you going deaf?
I said I'm done.

41
00:04:44,570 --> 00:04:47,000
How can you just
drop it like that?

42
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,500
It's a waste of time.

43
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:53,720
Your time?
I've wasted more than just time.

44
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,480
I went all out and dated a guy.

45
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,720
Guy is my best friend.

46
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,350
I was willing to lose a friend
so you could write a novel.

47
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:06,960
Well, now you don't
have to force yourself.

48
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:10,920
But didn't we do all this
to save the house?

49
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,640
Don't give up now, Grandpa.

50
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,560
It's not that.

51
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,800
I've talked to the bank.

52
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:23,120
They cut the payments
and extend the term of the loan.

53
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:27,999
Extend? So what?
We still have no money to pay them.

54
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,320
It's why I'm thinking
of a new way.

55
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,759
Save, what's going on here?

56
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:35,199
We heard it all the way
from the kitchen.

57
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,799
Dad, he's gonna stop
writing the novel.

58
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,640
- Aw?
- Sounds good to me.

59
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,960
Sound good?
It could bring in a lot of money.

60
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,760
Hey, the novel could be a flop.

61
00:05:51,260 --> 00:05:52,280
How could you know?

62
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,200
You haven't finished it.

63
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,280
It's not even published yet.

64
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:02,920
Save, please stop.

65
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:07,480
I wanna help too, okay?
I know we must do something...

66
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:10,730
or we'll lose the house, right?

67
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,040
Grandpa.

68
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,520
You promised Khun Tiad, right?

69
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,840
Aren't you ashamed to break it?

70
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:24,330
I told you, I'm done.
Forget about it.

71
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,240
Stop nagging me, will you?

72
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,520
I get that it's hard.

73
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:33,840
But I believed

74
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,000
that you could do it.

75
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:41,320
If you don't believe in yourself,
I have nothing more to say.

76
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,200
Save.

77
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:47,320
Watch your tone.
Apologize to him right now.

78
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,400
Forget him.

79
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,880
I know kids these days.
They don't care. Young or old.

80
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,560
It's okay, Father.

81
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,780
If you don't want to write,
it's okay.

82
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:02,800
Our snack business is doing well,
both the shop and online.

83
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:07,440
Little by little, we can certainly
put that toward the bank payments.

84
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:14,720
I'm sorry, Grandfather. I failed.

85
00:08:16,110 --> 00:08:20,010
But I'll find another way
to come up with the money.

86
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:48,400
Ahem.

87
00:08:57,110 --> 00:08:58,650
Oh, come on.

88
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:02,400
Four of us here,
and only Save got the drink?

89
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,680
What's that about?

90
00:09:05,430 --> 00:09:07,839
Never heard of a BL term?

91
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,360
Aw... how sweet.

92
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:14,920
- Just look at them.
- I'm melting.

93
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:16,439
Will you cut it out?

94
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:19,559
Come on, you're flustered.
You don't have to act mad.

95
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,280
Aw... come on, smile.

96
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,119
- Hey, hey.
- Hey.

97
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,120
Stop right there.

98
00:09:29,730 --> 00:09:32,960
I didn't know you guys were here.
Take mine.

99
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,100
- Sure, sure.
- Thanks, buddy.

100
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,680
Thanks for sharing.

101
00:09:39,570 --> 00:09:41,200
That's more like it.

102
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,600
Get back to studying.

103
00:09:48,490 --> 00:09:51,560
So annoying those guys.
Enough with the teasing already.

104
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,560
Just let them be.

105
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:56,870
Did something happen?
You seem wound up today.

106
00:09:57,490 --> 00:09:59,800
Ugh, it's just so hot out.

107
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:09,880
Hey, don't be silly. Put that away.

108
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,760
I just feel like it.

109
00:10:12,290 --> 00:10:14,120
Someone could see you. Put it away.

110
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:16,320
Nobody's around.

111
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,320
Guy.

112
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:27,440
You said I could go all out
with you when we're alone.

113
00:10:37,430 --> 00:10:38,560
Huh.

114
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:45,720
Wow, that's pricey.

115
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,160
What?

116
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,280
That art toy I've been wanting.

117
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:52,480
Pakka by PYT Room.
Way out of my orbit.

118
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,400
Huh.

119
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,520
Mm-hmm.

120
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:13,800
What kind of work is out there
for a 75-year-old?

121
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:21,720
"There's actually quite a bit
a 75-year-old can still do."

122
00:11:22,130 --> 00:11:26,760
"Light work from home,
like handcrafts, cooking,"

123
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:29,440
"or even selling plants."

124
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:36,200
Anything that pays well?

125
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:42,080
"That could be hard to come by."

126
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:44,559
"But it's not
out of the question either."

127
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,760
"Work that draws on
past experience, for instance."

128
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:50,439
"Former teachers,
professors, lawyers,"

129
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,519
"doctors, engineers."

130
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:55,199
"Any of those can
launch an online course."

131
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:59,760
"Income could range from
10,000 to 100,000 baht a month."

132
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,520
Hmm.

133
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,350
I was never in any of those fields.

134
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:18,640
"Then what did you do?
Anything you're good at?"

135
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:24,610
Hmm.

136
00:13:20,260 --> 00:13:23,720
Actually, it's better that
he's quitting the BL novel.

137
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,720
I think so too.

138
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:29,759
How could he keep up
with the young ones, really?

139
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,580
- Right?
- Mm-hmm.

140
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:36,320
At his age, he doesn't need to work.
Just sit around, and that's it.

141
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:40,279
Right. He can barely even walk now.

142
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,280
- Really?
- Yeah.

143
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:46,000
And lately, I've noticed
he keeps dropping things too.

144
00:13:46,780 --> 00:13:48,920
Oh, I hadn't caught that.

145
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:45,920
This is it when we get old,
huh, Mom?

146
00:14:52,690 --> 00:14:53,690
Before long,

147
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:58,560
I'll be sitting still like a statue
just like you.

148
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:16,720
Good afternoon, Grandfather.

149
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,500
Oh, hello.

150
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,680
Great-grandma, how are you?

151
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,150
Good afternoon, Great-grandmother.

152
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:34,760
Aw... being nicer to him, huh?

153
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,240
Serves you right.

154
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,080
Let's go live.

155
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:01,240
Alright, everyone,
today's special promotion is

156
00:16:01,590 --> 00:16:03,600
buy five, get one free.

157
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,840
Limited stock.
Once it's gone, it's gone.

158
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,720
Get your orders in now.

159
00:16:13,190 --> 00:16:15,520
Phi Save isn't smiling today.

160
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,600
Are you two fighting?

161
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,120
Are you mad at me?

162
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:30,140
No.

163
00:16:32,990 --> 00:16:35,640
Everyone, get the sales going.

164
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,520
Don't wait. Don't hesitate.
Hit that button fast.

165
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,399
New deal, everyone.

166
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,640
If we hit 10,000 hearts, I'll plant
a kiss on Save's cheek live.

167
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:45,460
Whatchu doing?

168
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,720
Let's hit it, everyone.

169
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:51,800
I'm not playing along.

170
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:53,800
Why not?

171
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,840
9,000 hearts, everyone.

172
00:16:59,890 --> 00:17:01,920
9,900...

173
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,640
10,000 hearts.

174
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,160
Hey, Guy.

175
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:10,960
What were you thinking?

176
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:17,950
Nothing to see here.

177
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:20,480
He just went to the restroom.

178
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:22,960
Hey.

179
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,490
"Use of restricted terms detected"
What's going on?

180
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,520
What's with you, Save?

181
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:42,880
No, what's with you?

182
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:47,200
I was just doing it for fun.
Numbers were flatlining.

183
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:49,160
I wasn't actually going to do it.

184
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:50,880
It wasn't fun for me.

185
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:54,090
Save, what is actually
wrong with you?

186
00:17:54,110 --> 00:17:56,110
Are you mad at someone
and taking it out on me?

187
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:01,960
Or wait, are you fighting
with your grandfather?

188
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:04,200
I saw something's off
between you two.

189
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:13,000
You can go now.
We've come as far as we can.

190
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,000
Get out.

191
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,080
I said get out.

192
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:19,800
Out.

193
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:35,020
Ugh.

194
00:19:26,060 --> 00:19:27,150
"Pakka, 4,500 baht."

195
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,240
Wow, that's steep.

196
00:19:34,020 --> 00:19:35,720
"Account Balance: 5,523.00."

197
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:44,880
One Pakka, please.
Can I get it today?

198
00:20:10,540 --> 00:20:12,520
Save.

199
00:20:13,970 --> 00:20:17,680
Guy said the channel got banned
because you dropped a swear word.

200
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:21,480
The cart got wiped out.
We can't do live streams anymore.

201
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:23,840
Sorry, Mom.

202
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:28,210
I will... get the channel back.

203
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,240
What were you two
even fighting about?

204
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:37,360
Can't you talk it out?
He's been nothing but helpful.

205
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,640
Huh.

206
00:20:39,410 --> 00:20:41,840
Well... we don't
need his help anymore.

207
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,560
Grandpa's quit the novel anyway.

208
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:47,500
No point in me
keeping going with him.

209
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:51,880
Save.

210
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,440
Go that way.

211
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,000
Grandpa, Grandpa.

212
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,720
The clip of you and Phi Save
went viral.

213
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:21,040
What clip?

214
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:40,040
"We're gonna hear from a grandpa
and his grandson."

215
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:48,079
One at a time.

216
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:51,680
The catch is
you can't hear each other.

217
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,330
Okay.

218
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:55,160
The headphones go on you first.

219
00:22:58,270 --> 00:22:59,270
Oh, sure.

220
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:06,080
Okay?

221
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:10,560
"Tell us about your grandson."

222
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:12,610
"He's a sharp kid."

223
00:23:13,290 --> 00:23:15,770
"Bright, quick-witted."

224
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,640
"Most of it he got
from me, of course."

225
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:22,560
"He can be a handful sometimes."

226
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:26,160
"But he's never said
a bad word about me."

227
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:31,000
"What do you admire most about him?"

228
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:32,800
"Quite a lot, really."

229
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:36,600
"On the surface,
he doesn't care about much."

230
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,920
"But deep down he's genuinely kind."

231
00:23:39,580 --> 00:23:42,280
"Generous, family-first."

232
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:44,840
"He's always looked out for me."

233
00:23:56,130 --> 00:23:57,760
"Now tell us
about your grandfather."

234
00:23:57,900 --> 00:24:00,160
"The most stubborn man
in the house."

235
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:02,920
Hey, be nice.

236
00:24:03,370 --> 00:24:06,240
"He puts on a tough front.
But that's all it is, a front."

237
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:09,000
No one looks out for his family
like he does.

238
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:12,080
"What do you admire most about him?"

239
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,560
"He is brilliant."

240
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:15,920
"My idol."

241
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:27,300
- Huh.
- Hmm?

242
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,320
No live streams for a week now.

243
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:35,260
Don't know if we can
get the channel back.

244
00:24:36,290 --> 00:24:38,880
Save says we're waiting on
their email.

245
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:41,240
Don't worry, Mart.

246
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:44,240
We're still doing good
on consignment, right?

247
00:24:45,040 --> 00:24:46,720
Well enough, I suppose.

248
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:49,320
We'll get the channel back.

249
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:51,280
Hmm.

250
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,840
Phi Sorn, why did you come back?

251
00:24:59,330 --> 00:25:02,000
Wait, why did you get these back?

252
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:06,080
The shop returned them.
Said it's not moving.

253
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:07,280
- What?
- Hey?

254
00:25:08,090 --> 00:25:09,879
How is that possible?

255
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:12,080
It was going well last week.

256
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:21,760
Hello, I'm here to restock.

257
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:24,560
I'm sorry, we can't
take more right now.

258
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:26,760
We still have quite a lot left.

259
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:29,880
Really?

260
00:25:33,340 --> 00:25:34,340
See for yourself.

261
00:25:34,690 --> 00:25:37,720
Ha? How's this possible?

262
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,840
Last week, they were sold out.

263
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:43,839
A new vendor came in,
selling at a lower price.

264
00:25:43,840 --> 00:25:47,360
Same flavor and packaging as yours.

265
00:25:55,060 --> 00:25:56,060
Here, look.

266
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:58,680
What?

267
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:05,960
Hey.

268
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:11,460
They even copied our logo.

269
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:15,420
People these days,
shameless copycats.

270
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:19,320
The only shop still carrying us
is Sun's friend's.

271
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:20,400
Just one shop now.

272
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,060
Why is this happening?

273
00:26:27,550 --> 00:26:29,980
Everything was starting
to come together.

274
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,560
And now...

275
00:26:32,290 --> 00:26:35,600
with no money coming in,
how many months do we have left?

276
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:43,460
Huh.

277
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:45,360
With what we've got right now,

278
00:26:45,850 --> 00:26:48,250
probably two more months.

279
00:26:48,470 --> 00:26:49,800
What? Two months?

280
00:26:53,060 --> 00:26:57,120
Then, we'll need to notify
the children's guardians.

281
00:26:57,440 --> 00:27:00,400
If we have to close, they must
find somewhere else to go.

282
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:03,260
We'll have to let them know.

283
00:27:05,340 --> 00:27:07,760
Where are we going to send them?

284
00:27:08,180 --> 00:27:10,200
We should start finding them
new places to stay.

285
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:24,280
Aw... my plants just can't grow.

286
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,679
You're not doing it right.

287
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:28,660
- Haha.
- Haha.

288
00:27:28,690 --> 00:27:32,439
Look who's talking.
Yours are the most wilted of all.

289
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:34,240
Yeah, look at yours.

290
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:39,920
Guys, guys.

291
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:44,800
This is bad. It's all bad.

292
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:45,970
Yeah, it's all bad.

293
00:27:46,130 --> 00:27:48,920
Let's replant them,
or we'll have nothing to eat.

294
00:27:49,150 --> 00:27:51,600
Not the vegetables. It's us.

295
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:55,960
I heard the adults talking.
This place is out of money.

296
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:57,719
We must find a new place.

297
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,920
- What?
- What?

298
00:28:40,570 --> 00:28:42,840
We must sell all of these.

299
00:28:45,060 --> 00:28:48,560
If we do, we won't have to
leave this house.

300
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:53,320
You two are friends now?

301
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:59,680
- We're calling a truce for now.
- We'll settle it later.

302
00:29:04,650 --> 00:29:07,920
Today is finally here.
The day we have to fight.

303
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,960
Everyone here
is like a friend to me.

304
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:13,040
Like a true family.

305
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,280
I can't bear to watch you go.

306
00:29:16,350 --> 00:29:18,760
So we're gonna save Saeng Karun.

307
00:29:21,030 --> 00:29:22,030
Are you all in?

308
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,040
- Fight.
- Let's do it.

309
00:29:27,210 --> 00:29:28,210
Ow.

310
00:29:28,660 --> 00:29:29,660
Ow.

311
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:31,280
Ow.

312
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:33,559
What's wrong, Pipe?

313
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:36,560
My stomach... I've gone four times
to the restroom. Still hurts.

314
00:29:36,590 --> 00:29:39,470
Oh, dear.
You should've told me sooner.

315
00:29:39,490 --> 00:29:42,160
Let's get you
some electrolyte powder.

316
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:44,540
Come, come.

317
00:29:44,560 --> 00:29:45,800
Ow.

318
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:48,840
Ow.

319
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,440
Ow.

320
00:30:03,660 --> 00:30:04,660
Ugh.

321
00:30:05,850 --> 00:30:07,350
The kids so quiet today, huh?

322
00:30:07,370 --> 00:30:08,800
Yeah, you're right.

323
00:30:09,290 --> 00:30:12,400
Usually, they raise a racket.

324
00:30:12,850 --> 00:30:15,680
If it were like this every day,
we'd have it so easy.

325
00:30:15,930 --> 00:30:16,930
That's true.

326
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:17,960
Heh.

327
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:26,920
I'll take this, yeah?

328
00:30:27,090 --> 00:30:29,800
Right, the kids
are probably waiting.

329
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,480
Oh, Save.

330
00:30:37,150 --> 00:30:38,720
Has the email come back yet?

331
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:49,320
Please let us have our channel back.

332
00:30:49,990 --> 00:30:51,600
Please let that happen.

333
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:54,760
Huh.

334
00:31:01,250 --> 00:31:02,280
Snow.

335
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:07,680
Pipe.

336
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:13,680
Jedi.

337
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,240
Snow.

338
00:31:34,420 --> 00:31:35,420
Pipe.

339
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:40,360
Jedi.

340
00:31:46,180 --> 00:31:47,180
Snow.

341
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:55,760
Deu.

342
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:57,400
Jedi.

343
00:31:59,230 --> 00:32:00,230
Everyone.

344
00:32:13,410 --> 00:32:14,640
Mom, Mom.

345
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:15,800
Hmm?

346
00:32:15,870 --> 00:32:17,780
Mom, Auntie Oui, the kids are gone.

347
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:19,600
- What? How could that happen?
- What?

348
00:32:19,630 --> 00:32:21,240
I don't know.
They all just vanished.

349
00:32:21,260 --> 00:32:22,260
Hey.

350
00:32:22,340 --> 00:32:23,430
Come on.

351
00:32:23,600 --> 00:32:24,600
Oh, no.

352
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:33,240
Hey, where did they go?

353
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:37,440
Hey.

354
00:32:38,280 --> 00:32:39,640
Your snack bags, Mom.

355
00:32:40,060 --> 00:32:42,080
I thought you had put them away.

356
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:44,680
I thought you had already
handed them out.

357
00:32:44,700 --> 00:32:45,700
Hmm?

358
00:32:45,710 --> 00:32:47,750
So where did they go with the bags?

359
00:32:48,340 --> 00:32:49,360
Oh.

360
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:54,440
Yes.

361
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:58,280
Yes, yes. Thank you so much.
We'll be right there.

362
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,100
Khun On, our neighbor.

363
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:03,640
She saw the kids
selling snacks at the market.

364
00:33:06,340 --> 00:33:07,600
Oh, that's Pipe.

365
00:33:07,990 --> 00:33:08,990
Hmm?

366
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:22,560
Ah! He came to tell me
he had a stomachache.

367
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:24,770
Probably stalling
so the others could slip out.

368
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:27,920
Let's go to the market then.

369
00:33:28,970 --> 00:33:32,680
Wait, Oui, you stay.
In case they come back.

370
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:33,810
Of course.

371
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:35,680
- Let's go. What a headache.
- Go.

372
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,890
Khun (honorific) On.

373
00:33:44,010 --> 00:33:45,159
Have you seen the kids?

374
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:47,880
Over that way, and that way too.

375
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:50,240
They've been hawking snacks.

376
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:53,460
Go, go. Split up and find them.

377
00:33:53,670 --> 00:33:55,480
Okay, Save. Go with Grandpa.

378
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:58,199
No, I can manage on my own.

379
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:00,999
Dad, what if you fall?

380
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,670
- Save, stay with him.
- Hurry, Phi Sorn.

381
00:34:06,050 --> 00:34:07,640
Let's go, Grandpa.

382
00:34:09,990 --> 00:34:10,990
Thank you.

383
00:34:13,640 --> 00:34:17,080
- Auntie Mart's Sanae Chan snacks.
- Sanae Chan snacks.

384
00:34:18,550 --> 00:34:20,720
- Want a box?
- Excuse me.

385
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,719
Want some? They're really good.

386
00:34:22,720 --> 00:34:24,600
Auntie Mart's Sanae Chan snacks.

387
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:25,879
No thanks, not interested.

388
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,000
- Thank you.
- All right.

389
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:29,720
Would you like a box?

390
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:32,060
- Super delicious. Give them a try.
- No thank you.

391
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:33,080
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

392
00:34:34,990 --> 00:34:38,260
Auntie, please support us. One box?

393
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,839
- Want one?
- Just one box, Auntie.

394
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:41,960
- Not for me.
- Please, Auntie.

395
00:34:41,980 --> 00:34:42,720
- Okay.
- Okay.
No thanks.

396
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:47,000
Excuse me.

397
00:34:47,900 --> 00:34:49,000
Want a box?

398
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,800
No thanks.

399
00:35:02,150 --> 00:35:03,640
Not a single sale.

400
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:05,440
- Same here.
- Same here.

401
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:09,200
Hi, hi. Good-looking couple.

402
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:11,180
Would you like some sweets?

403
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:12,599
They're really good.

404
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:15,160
It'll help us a lot.

405
00:35:15,180 --> 00:35:18,000
- So delicious.
- Please throw us a lifeline.

406
00:35:18,750 --> 00:35:19,959
It's like a dream.

407
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:21,750
- Great price too.
- Please help.

408
00:35:21,780 --> 00:35:24,040
- Please, just one box.
- Take one with you.

409
00:35:24,060 --> 00:35:26,520
- So good, really.
- They're great.

410
00:35:27,460 --> 00:35:28,460
Huh.

411
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:31,360
I'm tired. We've been at it all day.

412
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:32,520
- Hmm.
- Nothing works.

413
00:35:33,070 --> 00:35:36,150
- We can't sell that way.
- True.

414
00:35:36,180 --> 00:35:37,180
What do we do?

415
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:41,760
Mabel, Yoyo, Jingjai. You ready?

416
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:43,120
- For what?
- Ready for what?

417
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:51,470
Grandpa, you should sit down
and let me look for them.

418
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:53,080
No.

419
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,320
Woo-hoo...

420
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:02,360
Woo... Woo.

421
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:07,480
What's over there?

422
00:36:21,220 --> 00:36:23,440
- Woo...
- Woo...

423
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:27,180
All right, kids.
I'll take three boxes.

424
00:36:27,220 --> 00:36:28,680
Hey, thanks.

425
00:36:31,700 --> 00:36:33,280
Here you go.

426
00:36:33,450 --> 00:36:34,880
140 baht. Wow.

427
00:36:34,980 --> 00:36:37,800
- Thank you.
- Thanks so much.

428
00:36:37,980 --> 00:36:39,660
Here, two boxes.

429
00:36:40,270 --> 00:36:42,040
Thank you very much.

430
00:36:42,340 --> 00:36:43,730
Thank you very much.

431
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:45,200
Hey, we've just made 150 baht.

432
00:36:46,570 --> 00:36:48,520
These are so yummy.

433
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:50,680
A taste you won't find
anywhere else.

434
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:52,560
- Here you go.
- I'll try one.

435
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:54,220
Go ahead.

436
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:03,640
Hmm, soft on the tongue.
Good going down.

437
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,640
How about the whole lot?

438
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:09,640
- Yes.
- Yes.

439
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:12,600
Thank you.

440
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:18,200
Grandpa, Grandpa...

441
00:37:33,530 --> 00:37:36,720
We sold all of them.

442
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:42,400
- Aren't we amazing?
- Our sweets got big thumbs up.

443
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:45,720
Let's go home.

444
00:37:51,330 --> 00:37:54,160
Snow, you roped them all in, huh?

445
00:37:55,620 --> 00:37:56,620
Okay. Let's go home.

446
00:37:57,720 --> 00:37:58,720
Come.

447
00:38:04,010 --> 00:38:06,160
Shouldn't you
look after them better?

448
00:38:06,500 --> 00:38:08,280
Yeah, child labor.

449
00:38:23,660 --> 00:38:26,400
Who was behind all this?

450
00:38:36,500 --> 00:38:37,600
It was me.

451
00:38:38,190 --> 00:38:39,190
There you go.

452
00:38:40,090 --> 00:38:44,990
I just... did what I could
to keep my friends here.

453
00:38:45,460 --> 00:38:48,920
But you shouldn't have done that.
It's not safe out there.

454
00:38:50,830 --> 00:38:55,240
Go to your room until you've
thought about what you did.

455
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:02,240
It wasn't just her.
I came up with the plan.

456
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:08,000
- Me too.
- Me too.

457
00:39:22,730 --> 00:39:23,980
Please don't punish them.

458
00:39:25,180 --> 00:39:27,500
They just wanted to help.

459
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:31,690
That's right, Director.
We love this place.

460
00:39:31,910 --> 00:39:33,670
We want to help.

461
00:39:34,390 --> 00:39:35,390
Right, everyone?

462
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:37,200
- Right.
- Right.

463
00:39:40,140 --> 00:39:42,160
For your help,

464
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:45,480
most admirable.

465
00:39:46,420 --> 00:39:49,760
I am deeply in your debt.

466
00:39:53,350 --> 00:39:55,220
We can help more, Grandpa.

467
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:58,320
Just say it. Whatever it is.

468
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:01,360
I'll hold you to that.

469
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:06,240
But from now on,
no more sneaking out.

470
00:40:06,740 --> 00:40:09,880
Do not put yourself
in harm's way again.

471
00:40:10,470 --> 00:40:11,560
Understood?

472
00:40:11,870 --> 00:40:13,720
- Yes.
- Yes, Grandpa.

473
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:22,080
Auntie Oui, why are you crying?

474
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:24,000
I was worried sick
about all of you.

475
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:27,960
You could've gotten hit
by a car out there.

476
00:40:27,980 --> 00:40:31,469
If someone went missing,
how would I live with myself?

477
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:33,280
I've raised you all myself.

478
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:39,240
I'm sorry for lying, Auntie Oui.

479
00:40:45,340 --> 00:40:49,840
Don't ever do that again.
I was so worried.

480
00:40:50,190 --> 00:40:51,800
- Yes.
- Yes.

481
00:41:41,220 --> 00:41:42,220
Grandpa.

482
00:41:44,290 --> 00:41:45,400
I want to apologize

483
00:41:47,100 --> 00:41:48,280
for saying those things.

484
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:51,040
It's alright.

485
00:41:52,630 --> 00:41:54,600
I was the one who dropped the ball.

486
00:42:01,380 --> 00:42:02,380
Grandpa...

487
00:42:03,530 --> 00:42:04,570
shall we start over?

488
00:42:05,930 --> 00:42:08,620
All these years,
Saeng Karun has kept its doors open

489
00:42:08,990 --> 00:42:11,590
because of the money
from your great novels, right?

490
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:16,680
You've done so much for this house.

491
00:42:20,290 --> 00:42:23,760
So? Any idea how to make money?

492
00:42:29,490 --> 00:42:31,600
Sitting around moping won't help.

493
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:34,920
Do you have...
a life coach or someone

494
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:36,470
who can help us?

495
00:42:37,320 --> 00:42:40,000
Life coach, what does that mean?

496
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:44,520
Someone who helps lift our spirits
when we're running low.

497
00:42:45,280 --> 00:42:48,480
Or just someone we can lean on
when we need to.

498
00:42:48,860 --> 00:42:49,860
Anyone like that?

499
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:15,880
Leaving your fate
in the Buddha's hands?

500
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:18,440
Think he can sort it out for you?

501
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,120
Why not?

502
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:23,400
If it doesn't work, no harm done.

503
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:28,360
But if it does, that's a bonus.
Right?

504
00:43:30,020 --> 00:43:31,760
Whatever appeases you.

505
00:43:44,930 --> 00:43:45,959
Done yet?

506
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:46,960
Not yet.

507
00:44:01,190 --> 00:44:02,190
Who is it?

508
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:04,560
An old friend, Nop.

509
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:07,250
Oh, what now?

510
00:44:07,860 --> 00:44:10,450
When you're stressed,
you think of a friend?

511
00:44:11,830 --> 00:44:14,520
Aw, Grandma's going to
feel unwanted.

512
00:44:16,810 --> 00:44:19,720
A man doesn't tell his wife
when things get heavy.

513
00:44:20,080 --> 00:44:21,960
A wife can be someone
a man leans on.

514
00:44:22,510 --> 00:44:27,320
Your grandmother has always
been my strength all along.

515
00:44:27,460 --> 00:44:30,079
Aww...

516
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:31,480
Sickeningly sweet.

517
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:35,120
- Save.
- Hmm?

518
00:44:35,140 --> 00:44:37,920
Give me just a minute of quiet,
won't you?

519
00:44:39,500 --> 00:44:40,400
Fwee...

520
00:44:40,401 --> 00:44:42,160
Oh, okay, okay.

521
00:44:42,780 --> 00:44:43,780
Heh.

522
00:44:51,900 --> 00:44:52,900
Nop.

523
00:44:54,340 --> 00:44:56,320
We haven't talked in a while.

524
00:44:57,270 --> 00:45:00,200
You're lucky you went before me.

525
00:45:00,760 --> 00:45:03,240
But if you'd made it this far,

526
00:45:04,480 --> 00:45:06,880
you'd have just as much
of a headache as I do

527
00:45:07,700 --> 00:45:10,060
with all this nonsense
I keep running into.

528
00:45:12,370 --> 00:45:15,120
Everything's just
so different from our time.

529
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:35,260
Hey, Nop.

530
00:45:36,080 --> 00:45:38,000
Hey, give that back.

531
00:45:38,030 --> 00:45:39,399
How do you write every day, Sak?

532
00:45:39,400 --> 00:45:40,400
Nop.

533
00:45:46,220 --> 00:45:47,220
Oh? A novel, is it?

534
00:45:57,210 --> 00:45:58,440
Hey, this is actually good.

535
00:46:00,160 --> 00:46:01,800
Ah-ha? Really?

536
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:03,320
Yeah. Is there more?

537
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:05,360
Just started it.
That's all there is.

538
00:46:06,520 --> 00:46:08,560
Finish it and send it
to a publisher.

539
00:46:08,880 --> 00:46:10,660
I'm telling you,
you could be a real writer.

540
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:17,760
I'd love that.

541
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:21,000
But I'm out of my depth with them.

542
00:46:24,990 --> 00:46:27,400
Who says? You're as good as them.

543
00:46:30,460 --> 00:46:33,880
You've got something
you can do anything with.

544
00:46:53,630 --> 00:46:57,440
Save, I'm sorry
for giving up so easily.

545
00:46:59,470 --> 00:47:02,600
It's okay, Grandpa.
It really is a challenge.

546
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,480
I'm not upset anymore.

547
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:07,919
I'm going back
to write the BL novel.

548
00:47:07,920 --> 00:47:08,920
What?

549
00:47:09,960 --> 00:47:11,960
No "what." You heard me.

550
00:47:12,160 --> 00:47:13,170
Are you serious?

551
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:14,560
Dead serious.

552
00:47:14,740 --> 00:47:17,540
Why? Do I look like I'm joking?

553
00:47:28,000 --> 00:47:31,720
Please, let Guy not be
too angry with me.

554
00:47:33,960 --> 00:47:36,760
Leaving your fate
in the Buddha's hands?

555
00:47:37,280 --> 00:47:39,960
Think he can sort it out for you?

556
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:43,880
Right now, this is what I can do.

557
00:47:44,960 --> 00:47:47,280
Sathu.

558
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:56,680
"Guy, you there?"

559
00:48:05,320 --> 00:48:06,360
Pick up.

560
00:48:07,700 --> 00:48:10,560
Hey, give it back. Stop it.

561
00:48:10,920 --> 00:48:12,560
- Give it to me.
- It's mine.

562
00:48:12,590 --> 00:48:15,760
- Come on. Give me.
- It's mine.

563
00:48:16,160 --> 00:48:17,800
- Let me see.
- It's mine.

564
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:19,600
- Hey, don't.
- Come on.

565
00:48:19,620 --> 00:48:21,240
- Hey, no.
- Let me play.

566
00:48:21,260 --> 00:48:22,999
- Stop pulling.
- I want to play.

567
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:24,870
- Pipe, Pipe.
- What is this?

568
00:48:26,040 --> 00:48:27,079
New toy?

569
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:28,080
Yes.

570
00:48:28,560 --> 00:48:29,560
Where'd you get it?

571
00:48:29,561 --> 00:48:30,800
Phi Guy gave it to me.

572
00:48:45,230 --> 00:48:47,200
Oh, hi, Phi Guy.

573
00:48:47,720 --> 00:48:48,720
Mm-hmm.

574
00:48:51,890 --> 00:48:52,960
Here, take it.

575
00:48:53,240 --> 00:48:55,840
Wow, it looks expensive.

576
00:48:56,180 --> 00:48:57,510
Are you sure?

577
00:48:58,310 --> 00:48:59,310
Yeah.

578
00:49:00,250 --> 00:49:01,520
You won't want it back?

579
00:49:01,920 --> 00:49:02,920
Want it or not?

580
00:49:03,050 --> 00:49:05,660
Of course. Thanks, Phi Guy.

581
00:49:20,400 --> 00:49:22,280
He is so kind.

582
00:49:22,600 --> 00:49:25,360
But he hasn't come around anymore.

583
00:49:25,590 --> 00:49:29,760
Can you tell him to visit us?
I want to play soccer with him.

584
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:33,879
And I'm vanishing.

585
00:49:33,880 --> 00:49:35,800
Hey, wait. Pipe.

586
00:49:39,560 --> 00:49:40,560
"Sorry."

587
00:49:40,700 --> 00:49:43,919
"The number you have dialed
is not available at this time."

588
00:49:43,920 --> 00:49:45,080
He turned the phone off?

589
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:04,880
Grandpa.

590
00:50:06,980 --> 00:50:08,440
Without Save and Guy,

591
00:50:09,220 --> 00:50:10,600
can you write the novel?

592
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:13,960
Your input has helped a lot.

593
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:17,790
But if you and your friend
are in a tough spot,

594
00:50:17,970 --> 00:50:19,560
I can find another way.

595
00:50:34,780 --> 00:50:36,160
Thanks, Nop.

596
00:51:11,300 --> 00:51:12,860
"1"

597
00:51:14,260 --> 00:51:16,120
Guy is my best friend.

598
00:51:17,640 --> 00:51:19,840
An old friend, Nop.

599
00:51:25,520 --> 00:51:28,360
Hey, Nop. The publisher wrote back.

600
00:51:29,050 --> 00:51:30,120
Read it to me.

601
00:51:38,130 --> 00:51:39,130
Sak.

602
00:51:39,960 --> 00:51:42,600
Congrats.
They're gonna publish your novel.

603
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:47,640
Aren't you happy?
You're gonna a real writer.

604
00:51:48,370 --> 00:51:50,040
Your dream is coming true.

605
00:51:51,890 --> 00:51:52,960
Hey, it got accepted.

606
00:51:57,800 --> 00:51:58,800
Let me see.

607
00:52:02,200 --> 00:52:04,360
Prasit, see?
Somsak Prasit.

608
00:52:04,750 --> 00:52:06,870
We are pleased to welcome you
as our writer.

609
00:52:19,510 --> 00:52:25,440
"Tall dense trees lined every step
of the rugged jungle path."

610
00:52:25,840 --> 00:52:30,880
"Tender leaves swayed
and caught the last light of dusk."

611
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:37,760
"Two men walked side by side,
deeper into the woods."

612
00:52:52,530 --> 00:52:57,400
"Their faces slick with sweat
and smeared with mud."

613
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:00,720
"Breath ragged and heavy."

614
00:53:01,800 --> 00:53:07,840
"Yet the strength between them
moved in perfect sync."

615
00:53:09,320 --> 00:53:15,080
"In their eyes, a bond reflected"

616
00:53:15,640 --> 00:53:18,120
"too deep for anyone else
to understand."

617
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:26,600
You patched things up with him yet?

618
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:28,520
Guy.

619
00:53:28,800 --> 00:53:31,320
Sounds like he's cut you
out of his life.

620
00:53:31,600 --> 00:53:34,559
Maybe it's time to
try a little harder.

621
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:35,680
What do I do, Grandpa?

622
00:53:36,350 --> 00:53:37,520
Make him something.

623
00:53:38,120 --> 00:53:39,120
I don't want it.

624
00:53:39,840 --> 00:53:42,920
You told me yourself that things
can't go back to how they were.

625
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:50,719
The world keeps
turning every day.

626
00:53:50,720 --> 00:53:56,039
And we keep turning in its play.

627
00:53:56,040 --> 00:53:59,280
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

628
00:53:59,460 --> 00:54:01,999
We just might see
the world within.

629
00:54:02,000 --> 00:54:06,039
Let's walk together, day by day.

630
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:11,040
Come take the step,
what do you say?

631
00:54:17,580 --> 00:54:21,199
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

632
00:54:21,200 --> 00:54:25,119
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

633
00:54:25,120 --> 00:54:30,159
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

634
00:54:30,160 --> 00:54:32,639
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

635
00:54:32,640 --> 00:54:35,439
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

636
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:40,240
And land where
our hearts both grow.

637
00:54:40,600 --> 00:54:46,519
The world keeps
turning every day.

638
00:54:46,520 --> 00:54:51,759
And we keep turning in its play.

639
00:54:51,760 --> 00:54:54,960
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

640
00:54:55,320 --> 00:54:57,799
We just might see
the world within.

641
00:54:57,800 --> 00:55:01,879
Let's walk together, day by day.

642
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:06,760
Come take the step,
what do you say?
